===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally a {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} depicting a man with a prominent mustache.

Later written {{m|zh|頿|tr=-}} or {{m|zh|頾|tr=-}}, a {{Han compound|須|此|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=beard|nocap=y}}, where {{lang|zh|須}} is the original form of {{m|zh|鬚//|tr=-}}.

In the modern form, a {{Han compound|髟|此|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=hair|nocap=y}}.

